    <node id="Warfarin">
      <data key="d0">Warfarin</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-185e181fe87408ed68fffee05c4bf2c1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-58ce513efff4e4279006c76309bbe13e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e7a9cdc05d05872d2efc5bf2a78744d8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7361a603e8f2f0aa1358a337cf72e362&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e349119c3189688316f142a76b2f2e86&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-052d9f2eb36a76fdb7920ef60341853c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-96246f0053db41bc6854767c93a37e6c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-41c3680a3ad5516d5e6dcd6d045f4ed9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e29dee1ec3e83daa8c3982ec784f54d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8a72bff6a2caadef59875d68cb6aee2c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a5a80498abe28fa59b46e83f179e390b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4d4798197d2ae5bc5e60e5d876f94f20&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-69b807472f4820ade4cbf3153e7e88b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0392546b4be8990b5651990bc3c882c3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-120f6a61156fe5cb9fa55fd78d0d09df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6c01ebde56aad2ac664ce27bcf95cd5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0d9df8319256ab3c418f8c73ac00fad8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-81ca909fcf7ec8b326421ab4d2766d19&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4c4689566af7f5f15132f08d3ceb0561&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b069602a5af98b264deec4706c5b286c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-be0afdf0753c12d1860d48df1a690238&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2258cc9d8db0680e066bcf3b3675f10c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-18b3a59bf7f5ccc18f7641e35b20249f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c5d390cb21e6dd1e2d80ae8661e921a2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8bfa6d6104ce651a3fa698d413435e00&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dbe7a4df275280a24a14fa22f341095f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2789d641115d5adedba14603fd459ede&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c675cb429137f1eae8fe9eda77046b5b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cbac6ca9c4de60d11284fef00668f6dc</data>
      <data key="d2">Warfarin

Warfarin is an anticoagulant medication used to prevent and treat blood clots. It significantly increases the risk of severe gastrointestinal bleeding when combined with Aspirin. Additionally, Warfarin interacts with Lisinopril, increasing the risk of severe bleeding. Furthermore, Warfarin has been known to cause melena in patients taking it.

Warfarin is also an anticoagulant medication that prevents blood clot formation. Its interaction with Aspirin increases the risk of severe gastrointestinal bleeding. This highlights the importance of carefully managing medications and potential interactions when prescribing Warfarin.

It's worth noting that there may be conflicting information regarding the specific details of Warfarin's mechanism of action or its interactions with other medications. However, in general, Warfarin is recognized as an effective anticoagulant medication for preventing and treating blood clots. As with any medication, it's essential to carefully monitor patients taking Warfarin and be aware of potential side effects.

Overall, Warfarin is a crucial medication in the prevention and treatment of blood clots, but its use requires careful consideration and management to minimize the risk of adverse effects.&lt;SEP&gt;Warfarin is an anticoagulant medication used to prevent blood clots.&lt;SEP&gt;Concomitant use with Warfarin significantly increases the risk of severe gastrointestinal bleeding due to synergistic anticoagulant effects.</data>
      <data key="d1">drug</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776248014</data>
      <data key="d6" />
