    <node id="Dysthymia">
      <data key="d0">Dysthymia</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Dysthymia, also known as persistent depressive disorder (PDD), is a chronic mental health condition characterized by long-term feelings of sadness and hopelessness, with no complete remission. It differs from major depression in its lack of distinct episodes of severe depression.</data>
