    <node id="Depression">
      <data key="d0">Depression</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Major depression, also known as major depressive disorder (MDD), is a mood disorder characterized by one or more major depressive episodes in a person's lifetime. It differs from dysthymia in its distinct episodes of severe depression.&lt;SEP&gt;A history of depression is a contraindication for using these medications.&lt;SEP&gt;Depression is a mental health condition affecting older people.&lt;SEP&gt;Depression is a mental health condition that can have physical symptoms such as changes in appetite or weight, similar to those experienced by individuals with cancer of the small intestine.&lt;SEP&gt;Depression may be a precursor or co-occurring condition with HHS.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8b090779071c8e7710d56eea47326cc5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-96246f0053db41bc6854767c93a37e6c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-81ca909fcf7ec8b326421ab4d2766d19&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d2d5a6443dbb30e119056feab0775e8d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-18b3a59bf7f5ccc18f7641e35b20249f</data>
