      <data key="d1">creature</data>
      <data key="d2">Newborns are the target population for administering HBIG to protect against Hepatitis B virus.&lt;SEP&gt;Newborns are infants within the first 28 days of life, particularly relevant to jaundice screening and management.&lt;SEP&gt;Congenital herpes primarily affects newborns, implying a direct impact on this demographic.</data>
