    </node>
    <node id="Surgery">
      <data key="d0">Surgery</data>
      <data key="d1">medicalprocedure</data>
      <data key="d2">The term 'surgery' refers to an intervention that alters the structure or function of a body part through manual intervention. This procedure involves making incisions in the affected area, enabling surgeons to diagnose and treat various medical conditions. Surgery can be performed for a range of purposes, including draining large or deep boils, treating cardiac conditions during emergencies, and addressing complications from Congenital Rubella Syndrome.

Surgery is a primary method for treating hemoptysis, where it may involve surgical resection of the tumor to remove excess catecholamines from the body. In some cases, surgery serves as the mainstay of therapy for subependymoma, particularly for symptomatic or imaging-unclear cases. The process also encompasses the repair or correction of damaged or diseased tissues and organs using manual techniques or instruments.

The medical intervention utilized in treating various conditions, including those affecting the heart, may involve surgical interventions to alter the structure or function of affected body parts. It is essential to note that surgery can be a life-saving measure for individuals experiencing severe symptoms associated with Congenital Rubella Syndrome.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-bc3be0f57c35828f9e0117d5662b266f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e29dee1ec3e83daa8c3982ec784f54d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b5e9845e20d871df006f7d0c1be182af&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-073142c11014525a0c579f8afe5d210b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d34c203854cfba3cb9cf614c9d8ccdb8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4c2f60b0b07450ee3d612a874776dd17&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6a515aaf39a914cff3fed8adab5aed9f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d42bbf8dfa816d2d519b8c597b4c29ae</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
