    </node>
    <node id="Stool">
      <data key="d0">Stool</data>
      <data key="d1">organ</data>
      <data key="d2">Stool refers to the solid waste expelled from the digestive system during defecation.&lt;SEP&gt;The stool is a waste product from the digestive system that consists of undigested food particles and other debris.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-58320e3f9e2aeb800e533ad8fd0fa94e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8442ec3153c9dbbd0097bc0cb7253340</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776220303</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Bowels">
      <data key="d0">Bowels</data>
      <data key="d1">organ</data>
      <data key="d2">The bowels refer to the large intestine, which plays a crucial role in digestion and the elimination of waste.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-58320e3f9e2aeb800e533ad8fd0fa94e</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776199943</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Hard Stool">
      <data key="d0">Hard Stool</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">A hard stool refers to the consistency of feces when it is difficult to pass during defecation.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-58320e3f9e2aeb800e533ad8fd0fa94e</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776199943</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Incomplete Evacuation">
      <data key="d0">Incomplete Evacuation</data>
      <data key="d1">symptom</data>
      <data key="d2">Incomplete evacuation refers to the sensation of not fully expelling stool during defecation, which is a symptom of constipation.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-58320e3f9e2aeb800e533ad8fd0fa94e</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776199943</data>
