    </node>
    <node id="Lifestyle Habits">
      <data key="d0">Lifestyle Habits</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Lifestyle habits, such as a sedentary lifestyle or poor diet, can contribute to constipation.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-58320e3f9e2aeb800e533ad8fd0fa94e</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776199944</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Medications">
      <data key="d0">Medications</data>
      <data key="d1">activeingredient</data>
      <data key="d2">Medications, such as certain antidepressants or painkillers, can contribute to constipation as a side effect.&lt;SEP&gt;Prescribed medications are crucial for managing the symptoms of depression. However, it is equally essential to understand how to manage side effects correctly.&lt;SEP&gt;Various medications, such as nitroglycerin and beta blockers, are used to manage symptoms of angina and reduce the frequency of episodes.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-58320e3f9e2aeb800e533ad8fd0fa94e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-81ca909fcf7ec8b326421ab4d2766d19&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-088da958fcb0ca39994299dfa8dfa6f8</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776222081</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Infrequent Bowel Movements">
      <data key="d0">Infrequent Bowel Movements</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-58320e3f9e2aeb800e533ad8fd0fa94e</data>
      <data key="d2">Constipation involves infrequent bowel movements, leading to hardened stools and discomfort.</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776199945</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Albinism">
      <data key="d0">Albinism</data>
      <data key="d1">condition</data>
      <data key="d2">Albinism is a rare genetic disorder characterized by the complete or partial absence of melanin production, leading to various physical and medical symptoms.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e7a9cdc05d05872d2efc5bf2a78744d8</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776200529</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Hair">
      <data key="d0">Hair</data>
      <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
      <data key="d2">White hair is one of the primary physical characteristics associated with albinism, often resulting from reduced melanin production in the skin and hair follicles.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e7a9cdc05d05872d2efc5bf2a78744d8</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776200529</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Skin">
      <data key="d0">Skin</data>
      <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
      <data key="d2">Hypo-pigmented or white skin is another common feature among individuals with albinism due to decreased melanin levels.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e7a9cdc05d05872d2efc5bf2a78744d8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-901a18e35bf1b6f8ab52eb117c4fd34a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f7c0f69e36eeb5da53429b84ed908e5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0f1e35113adef96daab1d4f09df53e68</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776200529</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Eyelashes">
      <data key="d0">Eyelashes</data>
      <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
      <data key="d2">White or hypo-pigmented eyelashes are also characteristic of individuals with albinism, stemming from the reduced production of melanin in the hair follicles responsible for eyelash growth.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e7a9cdc05d05872d2efc5bf2a78744d8</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776200529</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Photophobia">
      <data key="d0">Photophobia</data>
      <data key="d1">symptom</data>
      <data key="d2">Increased sensitivity to light is a common symptom experienced by people with albinism due to an underdeveloped iris that fails to regulate light exposure properly.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e7a9cdc05d05872d2efc5bf2a78744d8</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776200529</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Visual Acuity">
      <data key="d0">Visual Acuity</data>
      <data key="d1">symptom</data>
      <data key="d2">Decreased visual acuity in individuals with albinism can range from mild to severe, impacting their ability to see objects and navigate their surroundings effectively.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e7a9cdc05d05872d2efc5bf2a78744d8</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776200529</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Pink Eyes">
      <data key="d0">Pink Eyes</data>
      <data key="d1">ocularfeature</data>
      <data key="d2">Pink eyes, also known as ocular albinism, are a result of the reduced melanin production affecting the iris color.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e7a9cdc05d05872d2efc5bf2a78744d8</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776200529</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Iris Hypopigmentation">
      <data key="d0">Iris Hypopigmentation</data>
      <data key="d1">ocularfeature</data>
      <data key="d2">The hypopigmentation (reduced pigmentation) of the iris in individuals with albinism can cause noticeable changes in eye appearance and vision.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e7a9cdc05d05872d2efc5bf2a78744d8</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776200529</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Strabismus">
      <data key="d0">Strabismus</data>
      <data key="d1">symptom</data>
      <data key="d2">A condition known as strabismus, or crossed eyes, is a common feature among people with albinism due to an unaligned visual axis caused by the altered structure of the eyeball or brain.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e7a9cdc05d05872d2efc5bf2a78744d8</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776200529</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="COX-1 Enzymes">
      <data key="d0">COX-1 Enzymes</data>
      <data key="d1">mechanism</data>
      <data key="d2">The COX-1 Enzyme.

The COX-1 enzyme plays a crucial role in the process of inflammation reduction, particularly in relation to its interaction with aspirin. Aspirin's therapeutic effect is primarily attributed to its ability to inhibit the activity of COX-1 enzymes.

COX-1 enzymes are targets of the inhibition action by aspirin. The enzyme is irreversibly inhibited by aspirin, resulting in a long-lasting reduction in inflammation. However, the COX-1 enzyme itself does not play a direct role in the inflammatory process.

The exact mechanism of how COX-1 enzymes interact with aspirin is not fully described. Nevertheless, it is clear that the enzyme is targeted and irreversibly inhibited by aspirin, leading to a reduction in inflammation.

In some descriptions, it was noted that COX-1 enzymes are targeted by aspirin. However, these statements should be considered as part of a broader context regarding the inhibition action of aspirin on COX-1 enzymes rather than standalone facts about the enzyme itself.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e7a9cdc05d05872d2efc5bf2a78744d8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7361a603e8f2f0aa1358a337cf72e362&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-052d9f2eb36a76fdb7920ef60341853c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-41c3680a3ad5516d5e6dcd6d045f4ed9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a5a80498abe28fa59b46e83f179e390b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8928c0908948420f48174742a70957ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8bfa6d6104ce651a3fa698d413435e00&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dbe7a4df275280a24a14fa22f341095f</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776241326</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Inflammation Modulation">
      <data key="d0">Inflammation Modulation</data>
      <data key="d1">symptom</data>
      <data key="d2">Aspirin helps to regulate and reduce inflammation in the body.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e7a9cdc05d05872d2efc5bf2a78744d8</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776200530</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Analgesic Effect">
      <data key="d0">Analgesic Effect</data>
      <data key="d1">medicalprocedure</data>
      <data key="d2">Pain relief is another therapeutic effect of taking Aspirin.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e7a9cdc05d05872d2efc5bf2a78744d8</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776200530</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="White Hair">
      <data key="d0">White Hair</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e7a9cdc05d05872d2efc5bf2a78744d8</data>
      <data key="d2">White hair and reduced melanin production are defining features of albinism.</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776200531</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Ocular Albinism">
      <data key="d0">Ocular Albinism</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e7a9cdc05d05872d2efc5bf2a78744d8</data>
      <data key="d2">The comparison of cutaneous features with family members is crucial in diagnosing ocular albinism, helping identify individuals who may be affected despite having more mild skin manifestations than those with pronounced ocular symptoms.</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776200532</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Cutaneous Features">
      <data key="d0">Cutaneous Features</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e7a9cdc05d05872d2efc5bf2a78744d8</data>
      <data key="d2">The examination and analysis of family members' skin features are essential in identifying the presence of cutaneous albinism in individuals who may not display pronounced symptoms.&lt;SEP&gt;Evaluating and comparing the characteristics of suspected patients with their family members is vital in confirming a diagnosis of albinism.</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776200532</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Family Members">
      <data key="d0">Family Members</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e7a9cdc05d05872d2efc5bf2a78744d8</data>
      <data key="d2">The examination and analysis of family members' skin features are essential in identifying the presence of cutaneous albinism in individuals who may not display pronounced symptoms.&lt;SEP&gt;Evaluating and comparing the characteristics of suspected patients with their family members is vital in confirming a diagnosis of albinism.</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776200533</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Aspirin and Warfarin">
      <data key="d0">Aspirin and Warfarin</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e7a9cdc05d05872d2efc5bf2a78744d8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-96246f0053db41bc6854767c93a37e6c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a037de6f2fcc6d8499a41fc6d0ae4590&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a5a80498abe28fa59b46e83f179e390b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0392546b4be8990b5651990bc3c882c3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7ba9ca889a884bf086782a96a1c01374&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0d9df8319256ab3c418f8c73ac00fad8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f7c0f69e36eeb5da53429b84ed908e5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-05a062c31232f7d983bd96c0052adfc7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e3a0c8e154e4ccec7970a27ed87dde58&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2789d641115d5adedba14603fd459ede</data>
      <data key="d2">The combination of Aspirin and Warfarin significantly increases the risk of gastrointestinal bleeding.</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776200533</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Genetic Mutation">
      <data key="d0">Genetic Mutation</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-e7a9cdc05d05872d2efc5bf2a78744d8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-865f279e1b6a3e8bf38bf34c9c655cb3</data>
      <data key="d2">Albinism results from a genetic mutation that affects melanin production, leading to various physical and medical symptoms.&lt;SEP&gt;Genetic mutations affecting bone growth and development can also lead to abnormal growth plate closure.</data>
      <data key="d1">cause</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776217331</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Diffuse Large B Cell Lymphoma">
      <data key="d0">Diffuse Large B Cell Lymphoma</data>
      <data key="d1">disease</data>
      <data key="d2">Diffuse large B cell lymphoma is a type of cancer affecting the immune system.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d2fa58799807a35ae2fb3f05639e3768</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776200578</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Laparoscopy">
      <data key="d0">Laparoscopy</data>
      <data key="d1">diagnostictest</data>
      <data key="d2">Laparoscopy is a surgical procedure that rarely uses for identifying diffuse large B cell lymphoma.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d2fa58799807a35ae2fb3f05639e3768</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776200578</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Diagnostic Test">
      <data key="d0">Diagnostic Test</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d2fa58799807a35ae2fb3f05639e3768</data>
      <data key="d2">Rarely used</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776200578</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Laparotomy">
      <data key="d0">Laparotomy</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d2fa58799807a35ae2fb3f05639e3768</data>
      <data key="d2">Rarely used</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776200579</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Bone Marrow Aspiration and Biopsy">
      <data key="d0">Bone Marrow Aspiration and Biopsy</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-d2fa58799807a35ae2fb3f05639e3768</data>
      <data key="d2">Commonly used</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776200579</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Liver Mass">
      <data key="d0">Liver Mass</data>
      <data key="d1">organ</data>
      <data key="d2">The liver mass being examined in a medical context is the focal point of this physical examination.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776201115</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Physical Examination">
      <data key="d0">Physical Examination</data>
      <data key="d1">medicalprocedure</data>
      <data key="d2">A comprehensive medical evaluation that includes multiple checks, including palpation, percussion, and auscultation, among others, to assess the condition of the liver mass.&lt;SEP&gt;A comprehensive physical examination is necessary to detect subarachnoid hemorrhage and monitor patient response to treatment.&lt;SEP&gt;The physical examination for pleural effusion involves assessing symptoms and lung function.&lt;SEP&gt;The physical examination entails checking for signs such as pulsus parvus et tardus and distinct systolic ejection murmur.&lt;SEP&gt;A physical examination for a lung abscess typically involves assessment of respiratory and neurological symptoms.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5ddbc7f33848d62cd982cd6bdf687587&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c16a4c902adb4dbeda6878a55d31bfe9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-edfc413f95838bcb6bb18546eedcab43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e521741147e08defca5beb7c20e86d2a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9d30496543b843d6d1f4e7bb6b58caa1</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776222950</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Patients with Liver Mass">
      <data key="d0">Patients with Liver Mass</data>
      <data key="d1">person</data>
      <data key="d2">Patients who have been diagnosed or suspected of having a liver mass are the subjects of this physical examination.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776201115</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Lethargic">
      <data key="d0">Lethargic</data>
      <data key="d1">clinicaldetail</data>
      <data key="d2">A symptom associated with patients who may be experiencing severe illness due to their liver mass, affecting vital functions and overall well-being.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776201115</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Cachectic">
      <data key="d0">Cachectic</data>
      <data key="d1">clinicaldetail</data>
      <data key="d2">A condition characterized by weight loss, weakness, and a general decline in the patient's physical health due to chronic disease, such as liver failure or advanced cancer.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776201115</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Confused">
      <data key="d0">Confused</data>
      <data key="d1">clinicaldetail</data>
      <data key="d2">A symptom indicating altered mental status, confusion can be an early sign of serious illness.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776201115</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="High-grade fever">
      <data key="d0">High-grade fever</data>
      <data key="d1">symptom</data>
      <data key="d2">Elevated body temperature associated with infection, inflammation, or other acute conditions in patients with liver masses.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776201115</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Low-grade fever">
      <data key="d0">Low-grade fever</data>
      <data key="d1">symptom</data>
      <data key="d2">A mild and usually short-lived elevation of body temperature, may be present in some patients with liver mass but not necessarily indicative of serious disease.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776201115</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Tachycardia">
      <data key="d0">Tachycardia</data>
      <data key="d1">symptom</data>
      <data key="d2">A rapid heart rate, potentially indicating stress or strain on the cardiovascular system due to an underlying condition like liver failure or severe infection.&lt;SEP&gt;Tachycardia refers to an elevated heart rate often observed in patients with dengue fever.&lt;SEP&gt;Tachycardia, or an abnormally fast heart rate, can occur in patients with tumor lysis syndrome.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e84e51a732cb67800c6d62a6011dc86&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-49ab824223b2cb236dc5551487939dab</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776237305</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Tachypnea">
      <data key="d0">Tachypnea</data>
      <data key="d1">symptom</data>
      <data key="d2">A fast breathing rate that may indicate respiratory distress, hypoxia, or other complications in patients with liver masses.&lt;SEP&gt;Tachypnea, or rapid breathing, is another typical symptom of adult bronchiolitis.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1d8eaadff9998f5d836eb4756204827e</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776225343</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Decreased SPO2">
      <data key="d0">Decreased SPO2</data>
      <data key="d1">clinicaldetail</data>
      <data key="d2">Lower than normal oxygen saturation levels in the blood, which can be a critical indicator of severe illness or inadequate oxygenation in patients with liver mass.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776201116</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Chest examination">
      <data key="d0">Chest examination</data>
      <data key="d1">medicalprocedure</data>
      <data key="d2">A check for abnormalities on the chest wall and lungs to identify any secondary issues that may arise due to liver-related complications.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776201116</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Alopecia">
      <data key="d0">Alopecia</data>
      <data key="d1">sideeffect</data>
      <data key="d2">Hair loss associated with medication side effects, potentially used as a metaphor or marker in this context rather than an actual indication of alopecia itself.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776201116</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Rate of breathing">
      <data key="d0">Rate of breathing</data>
      <data key="d1">clinicaldetail</data>
      <data key="d2">The frequency at which a person breathes can be influenced by physical and emotional states such as stress and anxiety.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776201116</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Auscultation">
      <data key="d0">Auscultation</data>
      <data key="d1">medicalprocedure</data>
      <data key="d2">A medical technique involving listening to sounds through a stethoscope to detect abnormal heart or lung sounds, including those related to liver masses.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-743cfdf09792d3c6190a63afd0423e8d</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776201117</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Decreased breath sounds">
      <data key="d0">Decreased breath sounds</data>
      <data key="d1">clinicaldetail</data>
      <data key="d2">Reduced ability to hear normal breathing noises in the chest area, which can be an indication of fluid accumulation, edema, or other complications affecting lung function.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776201117</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Percussion">
      <data key="d0">Percussion</data>
      <data key="d1">medicalprocedure</data>
      <data key="d2">A diagnostic technique involving tapping on the patient's body with a mallet to detect abnormal sounds indicative of internal organ involvement, such as liver masses.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776201117</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Dull percussion">
      <data key="d0">Dull percussion</data>
      <data key="d1">clinicaldetail</data>
      <data key="d2">A sound produced by striking the patient's abdomen with a mallet that is dull and not resonant, often indicating the presence of fluid accumulation or liver disease.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776201117</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Reduced chest expansion">
      <data key="d0">Reduced chest expansion</data>
      <data key="d1">clinicaldetail</data>
      <data key="d2">The amount of space available in the chest cavity to expand during inhalation can be affected if there are abnormalities within the thoracic cage, such as liver masses pressing against surrounding structures.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776201117</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Caput medusae">
      <data key="d0">Caput medusae</data>
      <data key="d1">sign</data>
      <data key="d2">A visible indication of portal hypertension characterized by distended and engorged superficial epigastric veins appearing like a rat's tail on the skin surface.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776201117</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Liver scratch test">
      <data key="d0">Liver scratch test</data>
      <data key="d1">medicalprocedure</data>
      <data key="d2">A diagnostic technique to determine liver size, where the doctor marks the area over the liver with a pen, then waits for 15 minutes and checks the mark again. If the mark has faded more than expected, it indicates liver enlargement.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776201118</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Cruveilhier-Baumgarten murmur">
      <data key="d0">Cruveilhier-Baumgarten murmur</data>
      <data key="d1">sign</data>
      <data key="d2">A venous hum produced in patients with portal hypertension, which is a specific type of sound heard during auscultation that can indicate liver dysfunction or disease.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776201118</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Described as a venous hum">
      <data key="d0">Described as a venous hum</data>
      <data key="d1">clinicaldetail</data>
      <data key="d2">A unique and distinct description of the Cruveilhier-Baumgarten murmur, used to help identify this sign in medical practice.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776201118</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Percussion (again)">
      <data key="d0">Percussion (again)</data>
      <data key="d1">medicalprocedure</data>
      <data key="d2">A diagnostic technique involving tapping on the patient's body with a mallet to detect abnormal sounds indicative of internal organ involvement, such as liver masses.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776201118</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Dull percussion (again)">
      <data key="d0">Dull percussion (again)</data>
      <data key="d1">clinicaldetail</data>
      <data key="d2">A sound produced by striking the patient's abdomen with a mallet that is dull and not resonant, often indicating the presence of fluid accumulation or liver disease.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776201119</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Palpation">
      <data key="d0">Palpation</data>
      <data key="d1">medicalprocedure</data>
      <data key="d2">A manual examination technique where a doctor uses their fingers to feel for abnormalities in the body's tissues, such as swelling, tenderness, or masses.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776201119</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Abdominal distention">
      <data key="d0">Abdominal distention</data>
      <data key="d1">clinicaldetail</data>
      <data key="d2">The feeling of a swollen abdomen that can be indicative of an underlying condition causing abdominal pressure or discomfort.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776201119</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Tenderness">
      <data key="d0">Tenderness</data>
      <data key="d1">clinicaldetail</data>
      <data key="d2">A painful sensation in response to touch, often used to describe the location and severity of liver masses.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776201119</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Hepatomegaly">
      <data key="d0">Hepatomegaly</data>
      <data key="d1">clinicaldetail</data>
      <data key="d2">The enlargement of the liver, typically detected during palpation or auscultation.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776201119</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Splenomegaly">
      <data key="d0">Splenomegaly</data>
      <data key="d1">physicalfinding</data>
      <data key="d2">The enlargement of the spleen, which can be associated with portal hypertension or other conditions affecting the abdominal organs.&lt;SEP&gt;Splenomegaly refers to an enlarged spleen, observed in approximately 33% of patients with Plummer-Vinson syndrome.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e4be7ad6187377b3faeb10739c71599a</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776202280</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Peripheral edema">
      <data key="d0">Peripheral edema</data>
      <data key="d1">sideeffect</data>
      <data key="d2">A swelling that develops in the legs and feet due to fluid retention, often resulting from liver disease.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776201120</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Muscle rigidity">
      <data key="d0">Muscle rigidity</data>
      <data key="d1">clinicaldetail</data>
      <data key="d2">A condition characterized by stiffness or rigidity of muscles, which can be a symptom of severe illness or infection associated with liver masses.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776201120</data>
