    <node id="COX-1 and COX-2 Enzymes">
      <data key="d0">COX-1 and COX-2 Enzymes</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2f8e3840cde7d092cb7e453428087efd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e29dee1ec3e83daa8c3982ec784f54d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0392546b4be8990b5651990bc3c882c3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7ba9ca889a884bf086782a96a1c01374&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8928c0908948420f48174742a70957ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6c01ebde56aad2ac664ce27bcf95cd5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f7c0f69e36eeb5da53429b84ed908e5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-81ca909fcf7ec8b326421ab4d2766d19&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2258cc9d8db0680e066bcf3b3675f10c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e3a0c8e154e4ccec7970a27ed87dde58</data>
      <data key="d2">Aspirin functions by irreversibly inhibiting COX-1 and COX-2 enzymes.&lt;SEP&gt;COX-1 and COX-2 enzymes play a role in inflammation reduction, but their specific functions are not targeted by Aspirin directly.&lt;SEP&gt;COX-1 and COX-2 enzymes are involved in inflammation reduction but not directly targeted by Aspirin.</data>
      <data key="d1">mechanism</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776229982</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
