    <node id="Dry Cough">
      <data key="d0">Dry Cough</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fa7b0387cb6903fcd84f7bdac107fe37&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4d4798197d2ae5bc5e60e5d876f94f20&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-69b807472f4820ade4cbf3153e7e88b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-120f6a61156fe5cb9fa55fd78d0d09df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-81ca909fcf7ec8b326421ab4d2766d19&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0535e5dee668fb3fd6a4787bb7b0a649&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c675cb429137f1eae8fe9eda77046b5b</data>
      <data key="d2">The presence of a penicillin allergy does not necessarily imply an increased risk of dry cough.&lt;SEP&gt;A persistent dry cough can be both a symptom of and a reaction to some medications, including those used for treating acute otitis media.&lt;SEP&gt;Although mentioned in the original output, its relevance was diminished. This cough's context is critical for the patient's overall well-being.&lt;SEP&gt;A dry cough is often described as a sensation of something being stuck in the throat.</data>
      <data key="d1">symptom</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776248014</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
