    <node id="Ovarian Germ Cell Tumor">
      <data key="d0">Ovarian Germ Cell Tumor</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Ovarian germ cell tumor is a type of cancer that affects the ovaries and can be classified into two subtypes: benign and malignant. The classification is based on histologic features.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7361a603e8f2f0aa1358a337cf72e362</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776202083</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Benign Ovarian Germ Cell Tumor">
      <data key="d0">Benign Ovarian Germ Cell Tumor</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">A benign ovarian germ cell tumor consists only of teratoma, a type of tumor that contains several different types of tissues.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7361a603e8f2f0aa1358a337cf72e362</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776202083</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Teratoma">
      <data key="d0">Teratoma</data>
      <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
      <data key="d2">Teratoma is a rare type of tumor found in the ovaries and testicles, characterized by its abnormal growth of cells from three or more different tissue types.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7361a603e8f2f0aa1358a337cf72e362</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776202083</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Mature Cystic Teratoma (Dermoid Cyst)">
      <data key="d0">Mature Cystic Teratoma (Dermoid Cyst)</data>
      <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
      <data key="d2">A mature cystic teratoma, also known as a dermoid cyst, is a type of benign ovarian germ cell tumor that typically has a smooth outer surface and no significant symptoms until it ruptures.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7361a603e8f2f0aa1358a337cf72e362</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776202083</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Immature Teratoma">
      <data key="d0">Immature Teratoma</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">An immature teratoma is an abnormal growth in the ovaries characterized by its rapid development into various types of tissues.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7361a603e8f2f0aa1358a337cf72e362</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776202083</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Monodermal Teratoma">
      <data key="d0">Monodermal Teratoma</data>
      <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
      <data key="d2">A monodermal teratoma is a type of teratoma that contains cells from only one tissue type, which can sometimes lead to tumor growth and other complications.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7361a603e8f2f0aa1358a337cf72e362</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776202083</data>
