    <node id="Struma Ovarii">
      <data key="d0">Struma Ovarii</data>
      <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
      <data key="d2">Struma ovarii is a rare form of ovarian germ cell tumor characterized by the presence of thyroid tissue in the ovary.&lt;SEP&gt;Struma ovarii is characterized by the presence of thyroid tissue within the ovary.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7361a603e8f2f0aa1358a337cf72e362</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776202083</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Carcinoid Tumors">
      <data key="d0">Carcinoid Tumors</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">A carcinoid tumor is a slow-growing type of cancer that can develop from various types of cells, including those found in the ovaries.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7361a603e8f2f0aa1358a337cf72e362</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776202083</data>
