    </node>
    <node id="Neural Tumors">
      <data key="d0">Neural Tumors</data>
      <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
      <data key="d2">A neural tumor is an abnormal growth in the nervous system that can be benign or malignant and has different characteristics depending on its location within the body.&lt;SEP&gt;Neural tumors are abnormal growths within the nervous system, often requiring separate consideration and treatment protocols.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7361a603e8f2f0aa1358a337cf72e362</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776202083</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Dysgerminoma">
      <data key="d0">Dysgerminoma</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Dysgerminoma is a rare type of ovarian germ cell cancer characterized by the rapid development of cells into several types of tissues. It typically grows slowly and can be treated with surgery.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7361a603e8f2f0aa1358a337cf72e362</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776202083</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Yolk Sac Tumor">
      <data key="d0">Yolk Sac Tumor</data>
      <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
      <data key="d2">A yolk sac tumor is an abnormal growth in the ovaries that contains cells similar to those found in the early stages of embryonic development, often occurring in children.&lt;SEP&gt;A yolk sac tumor contains cells similar to those found in early embryonic development and is often diagnosed in children.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7361a603e8f2f0aa1358a337cf72e362</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776202083</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Mixed Germ Cell Tumors">
      <data key="d0">Mixed Germ Cell Tumors</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Mixed germ cell tumors are a type of ovarian cancer characterized by the simultaneous occurrence of multiple types of germ cell tissues within the tumor.</data>
