    <node id="Pulmonary Edema">
      <data key="d0">Pulmonary Edema</data>
      <data key="d1">symptom</data>
      <data key="d2">Pulmonary edema is a condition characterized by excess fluid in the lungs.&lt;SEP&gt;Acute pulmonary edema with low cardiac output state requires inotropes, vasopressors, and/or mechanical circulatory support (MCS) to restore organ perfusion.&lt;SEP&gt;Fluid accumulation in the lungs leads to pulmonary edema, impairing gas exchange and hypoxia.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-b2df8254abbb9c5202e43d9e23991b28&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-be0afdf0753c12d1860d48df1a690238</data>
