      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Thrombosis">
      <data key="d0">Thrombosis</data>
      <data key="d1">physiologicalstressors</data>
      <data key="d2">Thrombosis, or blood clots, are a complication that can occur in patients with congestive heart failure.&lt;SEP&gt;Thrombosis is a blood clot that forms in a blood vessel, potentially leading to serious complications such as pulmonary embolism or stroke.&lt;SEP&gt;Blood clots in arteries and veins (thrombosis) are another factor that contributes to an increased risk of developing hyperosmolar hyperglycemic state (HHS).</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-331beb4d681443473668b1b86bc0a556&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-81ca909fcf7ec8b326421ab4d2766d19&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-18b3a59bf7f5ccc18f7641e35b20249f</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
