      <data key="d2">This condition is treated by using reserpine, hydralazine, and hydrochlorothiazide.&lt;SEP&gt;Coronary artery disease is a medical condition where the coronary arteries, which supply blood to the heart, become narrowed or blocked due to buildup of cholesterol-containing deposits called plaques.&lt;SEP&gt;Coronary artery disease refers to the narrowing or blockage of the coronary arteries due to atherosclerosis.</data>
