    </node>
    <node id="Chemicals">
      <data key="d0">Chemicals</data>
      <data key="d1">cause</data>
      <data key="d2">Chemical burns may occur due to exposure to caustic substances like sodium hydroxide or ammonia.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a5a80498abe28fa59b46e83f179e390b</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776207343</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Friction">
      <data key="d0">Friction</data>
      <data key="d1">cause</data>
      <data key="d2">Burns can also be caused by friction from tight clothing, synthetic fibers, or rough skin.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a5a80498abe28fa59b46e83f179e390b</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776207343</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Electricity">
      <data key="d0">Electricity</data>
      <data key="d1">cause</data>
      <data key="d2">Electrical burns may result from exposure to electrical sources, such as faulty wiring or electrical appliances.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a5a80498abe28fa59b46e83f179e390b</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776207343</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Radiation">
      <data key="d0">Radiation</data>
      <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
      <data key="d2">Radiation burns can occur due to exposure to ionizing radiation, like X-rays or gamma rays.&lt;SEP&gt;Exposure to radiation may also increase a person's likelihood of getting lung cancer.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a5a80498abe28fa59b46e83f179e390b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dbe7a4df275280a24a14fa22f341095f</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776241244</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Extreme Temperatures">
      <data key="d0">Extreme Temperatures</data>
      <data key="d1">cause</data>
      <data key="d2">Burns can be caused by extreme temperatures, whether hot (e.g., scalding water) or cold (e.g., frostbite).</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a5a80498abe28fa59b46e83f179e390b</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776207343</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Inhalation Injury">
      <data key="d0">Inhalation Injury</data>
      <data key="d1">consequence</data>
      <data key="d2">Inhalation injury in burns may occur when the burn causes damage to the respiratory system.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a5a80498abe28fa59b46e83f179e390b</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776207343</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Warfarin Anticoagulant Mechanism">
      <data key="d0">Warfarin Anticoagulant Mechanism</data>
      <data key="d1">mechanism</data>
      <data key="d2">Warfarin's anticoagulant effects are related to its ability to inhibit vitamin K-dependent clotting factors in the liver.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a5a80498abe28fa59b46e83f179e390b</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776207343</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Percutaneous Coronary Intervention">
      <data key="d0">Percutaneous Coronary Intervention</data>
      <data key="d1">medicalprocedure</data>
      <data key="d2">Percutaneous coronary intervention is a procedure performed to open a closed artery following fibrinolytic therapy or using an adjunctive strategy.&lt;SEP&gt;Percutaneous coronary intervention (PCI) is a minimally invasive procedure to treat coronary artery disease.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fa7b0387cb6903fcd84f7bdac107fe37&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-88cd08eb7d49a30bc0bc72846f427aff</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776228426</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Fibrinolytic Agent">
      <data key="d0">Fibrinolytic Agent</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Fibrinolytic agents are used in STEMI treatment and may be administered in the setting of Primary PCI, Rescue PCI, or Adjunctive PCI.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fa7b0387cb6903fcd84f7bdac107fe37</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776207373</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="ST-Elevation Myocardial Infarction">
      <data key="d0">ST-Elevation Myocardial Infarction</data>
      <data key="d1">event</data>
      <data key="d2">ST-elevation myocardial infarction (STEMI) is a type of heart attack that requires immediate medical attention.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fa7b0387cb6903fcd84f7bdac107fe37</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776207374</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Coronary Stent Placement">
      <data key="d0">Coronary Stent Placement</data>
      <data key="d1">procedure</data>
      <data key="d2">Coronary stent placement is a type of percutaneous coronary intervention used to open a closed artery.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fa7b0387cb6903fcd84f7bdac107fe37</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776207374</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Closed Artery">
      <data key="d0">Closed Artery</data>
      <data key="d1">location</data>
      <data key="d2">A closed artery refers to an artery that has been occluded due to blockage or clot formation.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fa7b0387cb6903fcd84f7bdac107fe37</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776207374</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Rescue PCI">
      <data key="d0">Rescue PCI</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Rescue PCI is defined as the intent to administer a fibrinolytic agent in the setting of STEMI, and the performance of PCI for failure of the fibrinolytic agents is unintended.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fa7b0387cb6903fcd84f7bdac107fe37</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776207374</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Failed Fibrinolytic Therapy">
      <data key="d0">Failed Fibrinolytic Therapy</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Failure of the fibrinolytic agent to achieve reperfusion may necessitate rescue PCI.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-fa7b0387cb6903fcd84f7bdac107fe37</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776207374</data>
      <data key="d6" />
