    <node id="Ichthyosis Vulgaris">
      <data key="d0">Ichthyosis Vulgaris</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Ichthyosis vulgaris is an inherited condition characterized by dry, scaly skin.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7714b28896e0f4b35847062fac4e9375</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776207763</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Mosaic Lines">
      <data key="d0">Mosaic Lines</data>
      <data key="d1">symptom</data>
      <data key="d2">Mosaic lines are scaly patches found on the shins of people with ichthyosis vulgaris.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7714b28896e0f4b35847062fac4e9375</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776207763</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Fine White Scales">
      <data key="d0">Fine White Scales</data>
      <data key="d1">symptom</data>
      <data key="d2">Fine white scales can be observed on the forearms in individuals with ichthyosis vulgaris.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7714b28896e0f4b35847062fac4e9375</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776207763</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Rough Palms">
      <data key="d0">Rough Palms</data>
      <data key="d1">symptom</data>
      <data key="d2">Rough palms are a characteristic feature of ichthyosis vulgaris.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7714b28896e0f4b35847062fac4e9375</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776207763</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Severe Ichthyosis Case">
      <data key="d0">Severe Ichthyosis Case</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">A severe case of ichthyosis vulgaris involves widespread scaly buildup, sparing areas with sweat glands and reducing skin irritation.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7714b28896e0f4b35847062fac4e9375</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776207763</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Prickly Itch">
      <data key="d0">Prickly Itch</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7714b28896e0f4b35847062fac4e9375</data>
      <data key="d2">The build-up of scales causes "prickly itch" when sweating is required but cannot be achieved due to scaly buildup.</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776207764</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Dengue Fever">
      <data key="d0">Dengue Fever</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Dengue fever is a serious medical condition that requires prompt clinical attention.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-9e84e51a732cb67800c6d62a6011dc86</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776208057</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Postural Hypotension">
      <data key="d0">Postural Hypotension</data>
      <data key="d1">symptom</data>
      <data key="d2">Postural hypotension is a drop in blood pressure upon standing, common among dengue fever patients.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-9e84e51a732cb67800c6d62a6011dc86</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776208057</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Narrow Pulse Pressure">
      <data key="d0">Narrow Pulse Pressure</data>
      <data key="d1">physiologicalparameter</data>
      <data key="d2">A narrow pulse pressure (&lt;20 mm Hg) can indicate severe dehydration or capillary leak in dengue fever patients.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-9e84e51a732cb67800c6d62a6011dc86</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776208057</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Intravascular Volume Depletion">
      <data key="d0">Intravascular Volume Depletion</data>
      <data key="d1">consequence</data>
      <data key="d2">Intravascular volume depletion is a critical complication of dengue fever, necessitating prompt medical intervention.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-9e84e51a732cb67800c6d62a6011dc86</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776208057</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Patient">
      <data key="d0">Patient</data>
      <data key="d1">person</data>
      <data key="d2">A patient with dengue fever should be closely monitored for signs of severe disease.&lt;SEP&gt;Patients who undergo endometrial ablation are typically women with severe or prolonged bleeding issues.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-9e84e51a732cb67800c6d62a6011dc86&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e521741147e08defca5beb7c20e86d2a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-40324022a0e3a72859b0d0b0a9c2b089</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776217032</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Dehydration">
      <data key="d0">Dehydration</data>
      <data key="d1">consequence</data>
      <data key="d2">Dehydration is a critical complication of dengue fever that can lead to severe disease if left untreated.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-9e84e51a732cb67800c6d62a6011dc86</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776208057</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Capillary Leak">
      <data key="d0">Capillary Leak</data>
      <data key="d1">complication</data>
      <data key="d2">Capillary leak is another serious consequence of dengue fever, necessitating prompt medical intervention.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-9e84e51a732cb67800c6d62a6011dc86</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776208057</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Observation Period">
      <data key="d0">Observation Period</data>
      <data key="d1">consequence</data>
      <data key="d2">A patient with untreated dengue fever should be closely monitored during observation to track the progression of their condition.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-9e84e51a732cb67800c6d62a6011dc86</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776208057</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Hospitalization">
      <data key="d0">Hospitalization</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-9e84e51a732cb67800c6d62a6011dc86</data>
      <data key="d2">Patients with dengue fever should be hospitalized for close monitoring of their condition.</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776208058</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Urine Output Monitoring">
      <data key="d0">Urine Output Monitoring</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-9e84e51a732cb67800c6d62a6011dc86</data>
      <data key="d2">A patient not urinating at least every 6 hours may indicate intravascular volume depletion due to capillary leak, necessitating observation.</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776208061</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Severe Disease Observation">
      <data key="d0">Severe Disease Observation</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-9e84e51a732cb67800c6d62a6011dc86</data>
      <data key="d2">Failure to monitor for severe disease progression can lead to poor outcomes.</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776208062</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Warning Signs for Severe Disease Observation">
      <data key="d0">Warning Signs for Severe Disease Observation</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-9e84e51a732cb67800c6d62a6011dc86</data>
      <data key="d2">The absence of urination every 6 hours can serve as a warning sign indicating the development of severe disease in dengue fever patients.</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776208062</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Spinal Muscular Atrophy">
      <data key="d0">Spinal Muscular Atrophy</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Spinal muscular atrophy is a genetic disorder that affects muscle function and movement.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a090a02528c7fd927363160bab1bbd65</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776208535</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="SMN Gene">
      <data key="d0">SMN Gene</data>
      <data key="d1">geneticmarker</data>
      <data key="d2">The SMN gene, also known as survival motor neuron gene, plays a crucial role in the development and maintenance of motor neurons.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-a090a02528c7fd927363160bab1bbd65</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776208535</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Future Pregnancies">
      <data key="d0">Future Pregnancies</data>
