      <data key="d5">1776235903</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Pleural Space">
      <data key="d0">Pleural Space</data>
      <data key="d1">location</data>
      <data key="d2">The pleural space refers to the area between the lungs and the surrounding chest cavity.&lt;SEP&gt;The pleural space is the thin layer between the lungs and chest cavity where blood accumulation occurs in hemothorax.&lt;SEP&gt;The pleural space is the thin gap between the lungs and chest wall where empyema can occur.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c16a4c902adb4dbeda6878a55d31bfe9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6dafb4a051e19d074b1f7f9b7e5a69c4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-743cfdf09792d3c6190a63afd0423e8d</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776235903</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Low-Frequency Vibrations">
      <data key="d0">Low-Frequency Vibrations</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">Low-frequency vibrations refer to sound waves with frequencies below 20 Hz, which are affected by the presence of pleural fluid.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c16a4c902adb4dbeda6878a55d31bfe9</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776209589</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
