      <data key="d3">chunk-c16a4c902adb4dbeda6878a55d31bfe9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-743cfdf09792d3c6190a63afd0423e8d</data>
      <data key="d2">Decreased or absent breath sounds are a common finding during physical examination for pleural effusion.&lt;SEP&gt;Decreased breath sounds or abnormal friction rub may indicate empyema when listening to the chest with a stethoscope.</data>
      <data key="d1">symptom</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
