      <data key="d2">The concurrent use of aspirin with warfarin significantly increases the risk of severe gastrointestinal bleeding due to its antiplatelet effects, which exacerbate anticoagulation.&lt;SEP&gt;A combination of aspirin and warfarin for patients suffering from cystic fibrosis increases the risk of severe gastrointestinal bleeding due to enhanced anticoagulant effects.</data>
