    </node>
    <node id="Autoimmune Hepatitis">
      <data key="d0">Autoimmune Hepatitis</data>
      <data key="d1">disease</data>
      <data key="d2">Autoimmune hepatitis is an autoimmune disorder that affects the liver and is associated with abnormal imaging results.&lt;SEP&gt;Autoimmune hepatitis is a disease where the body's immune system mistakenly attacks liver cells.&lt;SEP&gt;Autoimmune hepatitis is a chronic disease characterized by inflammation of the liver which results from the combination of genetic predisposition and environmental triggers.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f965a8c1575bef6d2f7acd3341681f0a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-55b8b3e0477165e125f7f89d268a161e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a8230a17581fb3608a6fff89480a7498</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776235494</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Primary Sclerosing Cholangitis">
      <data key="d0">Primary Sclerosing Cholangitis</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">Primary sclerosing cholangitis is a chronic disease of the bile ducts, often misdiagnosed as primary biliary cirrhosis. It is also known as primary sclerosing cholangitis.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f965a8c1575bef6d2f7acd3341681f0a</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776211306</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Cholangiography">
      <data key="d0">Cholangiography</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Cholangiography is an imaging study that visualizes the bile ducts and helps diagnose primary sclerosing cholangitis and autoimmune hepatitis.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f965a8c1575bef6d2f7acd3341681f0a</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776211306</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Hepatitis">
      <data key="d0">Hepatitis</data>
      <data key="d1">disease</data>
      <data key="d2">Hepatitis refers to a broad category of liver diseases caused by inflammation of the liver.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f965a8c1575bef6d2f7acd3341681f0a</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776211306</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Liver">
      <data key="d0">Liver</data>
      <data key="d1">organ</data>
      <data key="d2">The liver is an organ located in the upper right side of the abdominal cavity, playing critical roles in digestion, metabolism, and detoxification.&lt;SEP&gt;The liver is an organ with special innate immune features, playing an important role in the induction and maintenance of immune tolerance.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f965a8c1575bef6d2f7acd3341681f0a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a8230a17581fb3608a6fff89480a7498</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776235494</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Primary Biliary Cirrhosis">
      <data key="d0">Primary Biliary Cirrhosis</data>
      <data key="d1">disease</data>
      <data key="d2">Primary biliary cirrhosis is a chronic liver disease characterized by progressive destruction of the bile ducts within the liver.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f965a8c1575bef6d2f7acd3341681f0a</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776211306</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Bile Ducts">
      <data key="d0">Bile Ducts</data>
      <data key="d1">organ</data>
      <data key="d2">The bile ducts are tubes that transport bile from the liver and gallbladder to the small intestine for fat digestion.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f965a8c1575bef6d2f7acd3341681f0a</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776211306</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Dysplastic Nevus">
      <data key="d0">Dysplastic Nevus</data>
      <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
      <data key="d2">A dysplastic nevus, also known as a lentigo maligna or lentigineous melanoma in situ, is a type of skin lesion that has the potential to develop into melanoma.&lt;SEP&gt;Dysplastic nevus is a type of mole characterized by a rapidly growing existing nevus.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7be69385a3c09d3b0d51dbc9a40450e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-99459c884b05410676ea284f38d1224a</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776218207</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Melanoma">
      <data key="d0">Melanoma</data>
      <data key="d1">subtype</data>
      <data key="d2">Melanoma is a serious form of skin cancer that can be prevented by taking certain measures.&lt;SEP&gt;One of several subtypes of carcinoma of the penis.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7be69385a3c09d3b0d51dbc9a40450e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0535e5dee668fb3fd6a4787bb7b0a649</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776247082</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Ultraviolet Radiation Exposure">
      <data key="d0">Ultraviolet Radiation Exposure</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Exposure to ultraviolet (UV) radiation from sunlight or tanning beds is a known cause of skin cancer, including melanoma.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7be69385a3c09d3b0d51dbc9a40450e1</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776211439</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Sunblock">
      <data key="d0">Sunblock</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">Sunblocks are topical products applied to the skin to prevent UV radiation exposure and reduce the risk of skin cancer, such as melanoma.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7be69385a3c09d3b0d51dbc9a40450e1</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776211439</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Skin Cancer">
      <data key="d0">Skin Cancer</data>
      <data key="d1">disease</data>
      <data key="d2">Skin cancer is a broad term for abnormal cell growth on the skin that can be caused by various factors, including UV radiation exposure.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7be69385a3c09d3b0d51dbc9a40450e1</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776211439</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Tanning Beds">
      <data key="d0">Tanning Beds</data>
      <data key="d1">location</data>
      <data key="d2">Tanning beds emit high levels of UV radiation, which can increase the risk of skin cancer.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7be69385a3c09d3b0d51dbc9a40450e1</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776211439</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Public Health Guidelines">
      <data key="d0">Public Health Guidelines</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">Public health guidelines recommend taking measures to prevent skin cancer, including using sunblocks and avoiding tanning beds.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7be69385a3c09d3b0d51dbc9a40450e1</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776211439</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Skin Cancer Prevention">
      <data key="d0">Skin Cancer Prevention</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-7be69385a3c09d3b0d51dbc9a40450e1</data>
      <data key="d2">Avoid excessive exposure to sunlight and use sunblocks when spending time outdoors.</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776211441</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Fungal Meningitis">
      <data key="d0">Fungal Meningitis</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">There is no established secondary preventive measure for Fungal Meningitis.&lt;SEP&gt;Fungal meningitis is a medical condition characterized by an infection caused by fungi affecting the membranes surrounding the brain and spinal cord, known as the meninges.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-104e30ec578f7f19e3c1af2cfb6529c4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8bfa6d6104ce651a3fa698d413435e00</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776237157</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Disease Management">
      <data key="d0">Disease Management</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">A set of strategies and techniques applied to manage or treat Fungal Meningitis.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-104e30ec578f7f19e3c1af2cfb6529c4</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776211656</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Preventive Measures">
      <data key="d0">Preventive Measures</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">The lack of established secondary preventive measures for fungal meningitis is noteworthy.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-104e30ec578f7f19e3c1af2cfb6529c4</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776211656</data>
