    <node id="Secondary Amenorrhea">
      <data key="d0">Secondary Amenorrhea</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Secondary amenorrhea is a condition characterized by a lack of menstruation that persists after menopause, pregnancy, or other periods where normal menstrual cycles would normally resume.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-120f6a61156fe5cb9fa55fd78d0d09df</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776212448</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Estradiol">
      <data key="d0">Estradiol</data>
      <data key="d1">hormone</data>
      <data key="d2">Estradiol is a type of estrogen hormone measured during blood tests to check for hormonal imbalances.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-120f6a61156fe5cb9fa55fd78d0d09df</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776212448</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Pregnancy">
      <data key="d0">Pregnancy</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-120f6a61156fe5cb9fa55fd78d0d09df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8928c0908948420f48174742a70957ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0bab54f62c7293bd7def813f67bdd11d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-18b3a59bf7f5ccc18f7641e35b20249f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8bfa6d6104ce651a3fa698d413435e00</data>
      <data key="d2">Secondary amenorrhea can be distinguished from normal postpartum amenorrhea by excluding pregnancy as a cause.&lt;SEP&gt;Pregnant individuals may be at higher risk for complications from E. coli enteritis.&lt;SEP&gt;Pregnancy is a significant event that may be complicated by cardiac disease.&lt;SEP&gt;Pregnant women are at a higher risk of developing hyperosmolar hyperglycemic state (HHS) due to physiological changes and potential complications during pregnancy.&lt;SEP&gt;Pregnant women are considered immunocompromised, making them more susceptible to infections such as fungal meningitis.</data>
      <data key="d1">condition</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776237157</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="CT Scan of the Head">
      <data key="d0">CT Scan of the Head</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-120f6a61156fe5cb9fa55fd78d0d09df</data>
      <data key="d2">A CT scan of the head is one of several imaging tests used to assess secondary amenorrhea.</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776212450</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
