    <node id="Acute Mast Cell Leukemia">
      <data key="d0">Acute Mast Cell Leukemia</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f97bf6f2d440a6860c629d7349816ee4</data>
      <data key="d2">The duration of symptoms determines whether acute or chronic mast cell leukemia is present.</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776218948</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Leukemia">
      <data key="d0">Leukemia</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f97bf6f2d440a6860c629d7349816ee4</data>
      <data key="d2">The presence of leukemic cells is a key aspect in classifying mast cell disease as leukemia.</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776218948</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Chronic Mast Cell Leukemia">
      <data key="d0">Chronic Mast Cell Leukemia</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-f97bf6f2d440a6860c629d7349816ee4</data>
      <data key="d2">The duration of symptoms determines whether acute or chronic mast cell leukemia is present.</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776218948</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="CMR">
      <data key="d0">CMR</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">Cardiac Magnetic Resonance (CMR) plays a significant role in diagnosing cardiac amyloidosis by providing detailed images of the heart's structure and function.&lt;SEP&gt;Cardiac Magnetic Resonance (CMR) can be used to measure heart volumes, blood flow and ventricular wall thickness.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c799d24d617f1a56ff415cb6c4023306&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c5d390cb21e6dd1e2d80ae8661e921a2</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776234585</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Cardiac Amyloidosis">
      <data key="d0">Cardiac Amyloidosis</data>
      <data key="d1">disease</data>
      <data key="d2">Cardiac amyloidosis is a condition characterized by the deposition of abnormal proteins in the heart, leading to enlargement of the atria.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c799d24d617f1a56ff415cb6c4023306</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776219015</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Atria">
      <data key="d0">Atria</data>
      <data key="d1">location</data>
      <data key="d2">The atria are chambers in the heart that play a crucial role in diagnosing cardiac amyloidosis through CMR imaging.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c799d24d617f1a56ff415cb6c4023306</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776219015</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Tricuspid Valve">
      <data key="d0">Tricuspid Valve</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">The tricuspid valve is an anatomical structure in the heart that can be measured using CMR to assess right atrial size.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c799d24d617f1a56ff415cb6c4023306</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776219015</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Mitral Valve">
      <data key="d0">Mitral Valve</data>
      <data key="d1">anatomicallocation</data>
      <data key="d2">The mitral valve is an anatomical structure in the heart that can be measured using CMR to assess left atrial size.&lt;SEP&gt;The mitral valve is a structure within the heart that plays a crucial role in its functioning.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c799d24d617f1a56ff415cb6c4023306&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ea34669e3dc11beced307b643d8c67a4</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776239400</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="End-Systolic Frame">
      <data key="d0">End-Systolic Frame</data>
      <data key="d1">location</data>
      <data key="d2">The end-systolic frame refers to the specific point in time when the heart is at its most relaxed state.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-c799d24d617f1a56ff415cb6c4023306</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776219015</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Elderly People">
      <data key="d0">Elderly People</data>
      <data key="d1">persongroup</data>
      <data key="d2">The elderly are the target demographic for managing depression at home.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-81ca909fcf7ec8b326421ab4d2766d19</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776219352</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Exercise">
      <data key="d0">Exercise</data>
      <data key="d1">activity</data>
      <data key="d2">Regular exercise can help manage depression in elderly people.&lt;SEP&gt;Exercise is an essential aspect of maintaining overall health, including managing aortic regurgitation.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-81ca909fcf7ec8b326421ab4d2766d19&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9505e0e92178b551cf9aa59f021d1c9b</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776246145</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Pleasurable Activities">
      <data key="d0">Pleasurable Activities</data>
      <data key="d1">activity</data>
      <data key="d2">Engaging in enjoyable activities enhances well-being and reduces symptoms of depression.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-81ca909fcf7ec8b326421ab4d2766d19</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776219352</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Good Sleep Habits">
      <data key="d0">Good Sleep Habits</data>
      <data key="d1">behavior</data>
      <data key="d2">Maintaining a regular sleep schedule is crucial for managing depression.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-81ca909fcf7ec8b326421ab4d2766d19</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776219352</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Early Signs of Depression">
      <data key="d0">Early Signs of Depression</data>
      <data key="d1">symptom</data>
      <data key="d2">Recognizing the initial warning signs of depression is vital for early intervention and treatment.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-81ca909fcf7ec8b326421ab4d2766d19</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776219352</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Suicide">
      <data key="d0">Suicide</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Depression can increase the risk of suicidal thoughts, emphasizing the importance of monitoring mental health closely.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-81ca909fcf7ec8b326421ab4d2766d19</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776219352</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Alcohol">
      <data key="d0">Alcohol</data>
      <data key="d1">substance</data>
      <data key="d2">Excessive alcohol consumption can worsen depression over time and impair judgment about suicide.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-81ca909fcf7ec8b326421ab4d2766d19</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776219352</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Illegal Drugs">
      <data key="d0">Illegal Drugs</data>
      <data key="d1">substance</data>
      <data key="d2">Illicit substance use can also exacerbate depression and negatively impact mental well-being.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-81ca909fcf7ec8b326421ab4d2766d19</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776219352</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Positive People">
      <data key="d0">Positive People</data>
      <data key="d1">persongroup</data>
      <data key="d2">Surrounding oneself with caring, supportive individuals can aid in managing depression effectively.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-81ca909fcf7ec8b326421ab4d2766d19</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776219352</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Caring Support">
      <data key="d0">Caring Support</data>
      <data key="d1">persongroup</data>
      <data key="d2">Trusted friends, family members, or support groups play a significant role in enabling positive interactions and emotional well-being for individuals experiencing depression.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-81ca909fcf7ec8b326421ab4d2766d19</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776219353</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="World Health Organization">
      <data key="d0">World Health Organization</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">The World Health Organization (WHO) is a primary source of information on mental health and depression.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-81ca909fcf7ec8b326421ab4d2766d19</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776219353</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Patient Support Groups">
      <data key="d0">Patient Support Groups</data>
      <data key="d1">organization</data>
      <data key="d2">Support groups play a significant role in enabling individuals with depression to connect with others who share similar experiences.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-81ca909fcf7ec8b326421ab4d2766d19</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776219353</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Crisis Hotlines">
      <data key="d0">Crisis Hotlines</data>
      <data key="d1">resource</data>
      <data key="d2">Crisis hotlines offer immediate help for individuals in distress, serving as a vital resource for managing depressive symptoms.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-81ca909fcf7ec8b326421ab4d2766d19</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776219353</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="High Blood Pressure">
      <data key="d0">High Blood Pressure</data>
      <data key="d1">disease</data>
      <data key="d2">High blood pressure, or hypertension, increases the risk of cardiovascular disease when left untreated.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-81ca909fcf7ec8b326421ab4d2766d19</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776219353</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Cardiac Disease">
      <data key="d0">Cardiac Disease</data>
      <data key="d1">disease</data>
      <data key="d2">Cardiac disease refers to disorders related to the heart's structure and function.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-0bab54f62c7293bd7def813f67bdd11d</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776219421</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Pulmonary Arterial Hypertension">
      <data key="d0">Pulmonary Arterial Hypertension</data>
      <data key="d1">disease</data>
      <data key="d2">Severe pulmonary arterial hypertension poses a significant risk for pregnant women with cardiac disease.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-0bab54f62c7293bd7def813f67bdd11d</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776219422</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Severe Fixed Valve Stenoses">
      <data key="d0">Severe Fixed Valve Stenoses</data>
      <data key="d1">disease</data>
      <data key="d2">Severe fixed valve stenoses refer to narrowed heart valves that do not open properly.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-0bab54f62c7293bd7def813f67bdd11d</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776219422</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Absolute Contraindication">
      <data key="d0">Absolute Contraindication</data>
      <data key="d1">contraindication</data>
      <data key="d2">Absolute contraindications are conditions where pregnancy is strictly forbidden due to risk of harm.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-0bab54f62c7293bd7def813f67bdd11d</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776219422</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Peripartum Cardiomyopathy">
      <data key="d0">Peripartum Cardiomyopathy</data>
      <data key="d1">disease</data>
      <data key="d2">Peripartum cardiomyopathy refers to heart muscle weakness or failure around the time of childbirth.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-0bab54f62c7293bd7def813f67bdd11d</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776219422</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Marfan's Syndrome">
      <data key="d0">Marfan's Syndrome</data>
      <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
      <data key="d2">Marfan's syndrome is a genetic disorder affecting the body's connective tissue.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-0bab54f62c7293bd7def813f67bdd11d</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776219422</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Severe Cyanosis">
      <data key="d0">Severe Cyanosis</data>
      <data key="d1">symptom</data>
      <data key="d2">Severe cyanosis is an abnormal bluish discoloration of the skin and mucous membranes, often indicative of poor oxygenation.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-0bab54f62c7293bd7def813f67bdd11d</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776219422</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Class III or IV Congestive Heart Failure">
      <data key="d0">Class III or IV Congestive Heart Failure</data>
      <data key="d1">disease</data>
      <data key="d2">Class III or IV congestive heart failure indicates severe impairment of the heart's ability to pump blood efficiently.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-0bab54f62c7293bd7def813f67bdd11d</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776219422</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Peutz-Jeghers Syndrome">
      <data key="d0">Peutz-Jeghers Syndrome</data>
      <data key="d1">condition</data>
      <data key="d2">Peutz-Jeghers syndrome is a rare genetic disorder characterized by the development of polyps in the gastrointestinal tract and increased risk of cancer.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8442ec3153c9dbbd0097bc0cb7253340</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776220302</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Iron Deficiency Anemia">
      <data key="d0">Iron Deficiency Anemia</data>
      <data key="d1">condition</data>
      <data key="d2">Iron deficiency anemia is a complication of Peutz-Jeghers syndrome that can lead to various health issues if left untreated.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8442ec3153c9dbbd0097bc0cb7253340</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776220302</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Gastrointestinal Tract">
      <data key="d0">Gastrointestinal Tract</data>
      <data key="d1">organ</data>
      <data key="d2">The gastrointestinal tract refers to a part of the digestive system that includes organs such as the stomach, small intestine, and large intestine.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8442ec3153c9dbbd0097bc0cb7253340</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776220303</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Growth">
      <data key="d0">Growth</data>
      <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
      <data key="d2">A growth is an abnormal increase in size or development, such as polyps in the gastrointestinal tract.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8442ec3153c9dbbd0097bc0cb7253340</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776220303</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Debris">
      <data key="d0">Debris</data>
      <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
      <data key="d2">Debris refers to small particles or fragments that are left over from a process or event, such as undigested food particles in the stool.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8442ec3153c9dbbd0097bc0cb7253340</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776220303</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Anemia">
      <data key="d0">Anemia</data>
      <data key="d1">condition</data>
      <data key="d2">Anemia is a disease characterized by a deficiency in red blood cells or hemoglobin, leading to insufficient oxygen delivery to tissues and organs.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8442ec3153c9dbbd0097bc0cb7253340</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776220303</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Hemoglobin">
      <data key="d0">Hemoglobin</data>
      <data key="d1">protein</data>
      <data key="d2">Hemoglobin is a protein found in red blood cells that carries oxygen from the lungs to the rest of the body.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8442ec3153c9dbbd0097bc0cb7253340</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776220303</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Stool Guaiac Test">
      <data key="d0">Stool Guaiac Test</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8442ec3153c9dbbd0097bc0cb7253340</data>
      <data key="d2">The stool guaiac test may help detect Peutz-Jeghers syndrome by identifying blood in the stool.</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776220306</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Blood Test">
      <data key="d0">Blood Test</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8442ec3153c9dbbd0097bc0cb7253340</data>
      <data key="d2">A blood test may be used to analyze stool samples for signs of disease or infection.</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776220306</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Polyps">
      <data key="d0">Polyps</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8442ec3153c9dbbd0097bc0cb7253340</data>
      <data key="d2">Polyps are abnormal growths on the walls of the gastrointestinal tract in Peutz-Jeghers syndrome patients.</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776220306</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Complete Blood Count (CBC)">
      <data key="d0">Complete Blood Count (CBC)</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8442ec3153c9dbbd0097bc0cb7253340</data>
      <data key="d2">A complete blood count (CBC) can aid in diagnosing Peutz-Jeghers syndrome by detecting anemia.</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776220306</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Blood">
      <data key="d0">Blood</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8442ec3153c9dbbd0097bc0cb7253340</data>
      <data key="d2">The guaiac test detects blood in stool by identifying the presence of heme, a protein found in red blood cells, which mixes with bile to form debris.</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776220307</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Bile">
      <data key="d0">Bile</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8442ec3153c9dbbd0097bc0cb7253340</data>
      <data key="d2">Bile is a digestive fluid produced by the liver and stored in the gallbladder that can mix with blood to form debris.</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776220307</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Serum Iron Test">
      <data key="d0">Serum Iron Test</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8442ec3153c9dbbd0097bc0cb7253340</data>
      <data key="d2">The serum iron test measures the level of iron in the blood to help diagnose anemia.</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776220307</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Serum Ferritin Test">
      <data key="d0">Serum Ferritin Test</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8442ec3153c9dbbd0097bc0cb7253340</data>
      <data key="d2">The serum ferritin test measures the level of iron stored in the body's tissues and fluids, which can help diagnose anemia.</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776220309</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Phyllodes Tumor">
      <data key="d0">Phyllodes Tumor</data>
      <data key="d1">tumor</data>
      <data key="d2">Phyllodes tumor is a type of fibroepithelial tumor that may be benign or malignant with large slit-like spaces within its structure.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4c4689566af7f5f15132f08d3ceb0561</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776220391</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Sclerosing Adenosis">
      <data key="d0">Sclerosing Adenosis</data>
      <data key="d1">benignlesion</data>
      <data key="d2">Sclerosing adenosis is considered a benign lesion but carries an increased risk of breast cancer due to the presence of small breast acini with collapsed lumens and fibrosis surrounding them.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4c4689566af7f5f15132f08d3ceb0561</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776220391</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="ADH (Atypical Ductal Hyperplasia)">
      <data key="d0">ADH (Atypical Ductal Hyperplasia)</data>
      <data key="d1">tumor</data>
      <data key="d2">ADH, based on a molecular basis, is classified as a low-grade DCIS (ductal carcinoma in situ) with localized proliferation. It is considered an atypical condition due to the presence of cells that display abnormal growth patterns.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4c4689566af7f5f15132f08d3ceb0561</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776220391</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Histopathologic Image (Source: Nephron, from Wikimedia Commons)">
      <data key="d0">Histopathologic Image (Source: Nephron, from Wikimedia Commons)</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-4c4689566af7f5f15132f08d3ceb0561</data>
      <data key="d2">The histopathologic image of Phyllodes tumor provides insight into its molecular basis, which aids in understanding its clinical significance.&lt;SEP&gt;The histopathologic image of Phyllodes tumor helps in characterizing its type and determining its potential for malignancy.&lt;SEP&gt;The histopathologic image is sourced from Nephron and Wikimedia Commons for Phyllodes tumor characterization.</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
