    </node>
    <node id="Dextro-Transposition of the Great Arteries (d-TGA)">
      <data key="d0">Dextro-Transposition of the Great Arteries (d-TGA)</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">A type of TGA that is referred to as d-TGA.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8e89c93cc380a668363623c506d07964</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776220972</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Transposition of the Great Vessels (TGV)">
      <data key="d0">Transposition of the Great Vessels (TGV)</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">A term with an even broader meaning than TGA, commonly used to refer to both l-TGA and d-TGA.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8e89c93cc380a668363623c506d07964</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776220972</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Aorta">
      <data key="d0">Aorta</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8e89c93cc380a668363623c506d07964&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ea34669e3dc11beced307b643d8c67a4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c43578074ab1eb1b44769dd9b14e451a</data>
      <data key="d2">The primary arteries in l-TGA are transposed with the aorta anterior and to the left of the pulmonary artery.&lt;SEP&gt;The aorta is a major blood vessel in the body.</data>
      <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776248473</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Synonym">
      <data key="d0">Synonym</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8e89c93cc380a668363623c506d07964</data>
      <data key="d2">Both terms describe the ventriculoarterial discordance in l-TGA patients.</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776220975</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Cause">
      <data key="d0">Cause</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8e89c93cc380a668363623c506d07964</data>
      <data key="d2">The term "corrected" has been disputed due to frequent occurrences of other abnormalities in l-TGA patients.</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776220976</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Clinical Indication">
      <data key="d0">Clinical Indication</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8e89c93cc380a668363623c506d07964</data>
      <data key="d2">The levo-transposition of the great arteries is a type of congenital heart defect.</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776220977</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Definition">
      <data key="d0">Definition</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8e89c93cc380a668363623c506d07964&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-83317cc68b9913276e42ed6006c923f7</data>
      <data key="d2">The levo-transposition of the great arteries is defined as an abnormality in which the aorta arises from the right ventricle and the pulmonary artery arises from the left ventricle.&lt;SEP&gt;The definition of polydipsia involves an abnormally increased water intake and/or decreased osmolality in the blood.</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776242264</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="SSRI">
      <data key="d0">SSRI</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Selective Serotonin Reuptake Inhibitors (SSRIs) are a class of medications used to treat various mental health conditions.&lt;SEP&gt;SSRI stands for Selective Serotonin Reuptake Inhibitor, which is a type of antidepressant medication.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-6fc0ac2cbfbe29731925a257279ee8f5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4548c5b111c364ce41f0561780435fec</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776246574</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Sexual Dysfunction">
      <data key="d0">Sexual Dysfunction</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Sexual dysfunction refers to disturbances in sexual desire, arousal, or orgasmic function.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-6fc0ac2cbfbe29731925a257279ee8f5</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776221108</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Libido">
      <data key="d0">Libido</data>
      <data key="d1">person</data>
      <data key="d2">Decreased libido can be a symptom of SSRI discontinuation.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-6fc0ac2cbfbe29731925a257279ee8f5</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776221108</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Impotence">
      <data key="d0">Impotence</data>
      <data key="d1">sideeffect</data>
      <data key="d2">Impotence is a condition characterized by the inability to achieve an erection.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-6fc0ac2cbfbe29731925a257279ee8f5</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776221108</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Vaginal Lubrication">
      <data key="d0">Vaginal Lubrication</data>
      <data key="d1">sideeffect</data>
      <data key="d2">Reduced vaginal lubrication can be a side effect of SSRI discontinuation.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-6fc0ac2cbfbe29731925a257279ee8f5</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776221108</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Difficulty Initiating Erection">
      <data key="d0">Difficulty Initiating Erection</data>
      <data key="d1">symptom</data>
      <data key="d2">Difficulty initiating or maintaining an erection is a common sexual symptom following SSRI discontinuation.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-6fc0ac2cbfbe29731925a257279ee8f5</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776221108</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Persistent Sexual Arousal Syndrome">
      <data key="d0">Persistent Sexual Arousal Syndrome</data>
      <data key="d1">sideeffect</data>
      <data key="d2">This condition is characterized by persistent sexual arousal despite the absence of desire.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-6fc0ac2cbfbe29731925a257279ee8f5</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776221108</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Anorgasmia">
      <data key="d0">Anorgasmia</data>
      <data key="d1">symptom</data>
      <data key="d2">Muted or absent orgasm (anorgasmia) can be a side effect of SSRI discontinuation.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-6fc0ac2cbfbe29731925a257279ee8f5</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776221108</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Ejaculatory Anhedonia">
      <data key="d0">Ejaculatory Anhedonia</data>
      <data key="d1">symptom</data>
      <data key="d2">Reduced or no experience of pleasure during orgasm (ejaculatory anhedonia) is another potential symptom.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-6fc0ac2cbfbe29731925a257279ee8f5</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776221108</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Premature Ejaculation">
      <data key="d0">Premature Ejaculation</data>
      <data key="d1">symptom</data>
      <data key="d2">Premature ejaculation can be a side effect of SSRI discontinuation.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-6fc0ac2cbfbe29731925a257279ee8f5</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776221108</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Penile Sensitivity">
      <data key="d0">Penile Sensitivity</data>
      <data key="d1">sideeffect</data>
      <data key="d2">Weakened penile sensitivity or genital anesthesia is another potential side effect.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-6fc0ac2cbfbe29731925a257279ee8f5</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776221108</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Priapism">
      <data key="d0">Priapism</data>
      <data key="d1">sideeffect</data>
      <data key="d2">Loss or decreased response to sexual stimuli, reduced semen volume, and priapism are also possible side effects of SSRI discontinuation.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-6fc0ac2cbfbe29731925a257279ee8f5</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776221108</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Selective Serotonin Reuptake Inhibitor">
      <data key="d0">Selective Serotonin Reuptake Inhibitor</data>
      <data key="d1">data</data>
      <data key="d2">Selective serotonin reuptake inhibitors (SSRIs) are a class of medications.&lt;SEP&gt;A term referring to a category of drugs used to treat depression.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-6fc0ac2cbfbe29731925a257279ee8f5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4548c5b111c364ce41f0561780435fec</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776246575</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Mental Health Condition">
      <data key="d0">Mental Health Condition</data>
      <data key="d1">content</data>
      <data key="d2">Depression and anxiety disorders are among the most common mental health conditions that may be treated with SSRIs.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-6fc0ac2cbfbe29731925a257279ee8f5</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776221109</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Neurotransmitter">
      <data key="d0">Neurotransmitter</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Serotonin is a neurotransmitter that plays a key role in regulating mood, appetite, and sleep patterns.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-6fc0ac2cbfbe29731925a257279ee8f5</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776221109</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="SSRIs">
      <data key="d0">SSRIs</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-6fc0ac2cbfbe29731925a257279ee8f5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4548c5b111c364ce41f0561780435fec</data>
      <data key="d2">Selective Serotonin Reuptake Inhibitors (SSRIs) can cause a range of sexual symptoms.</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776221111</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Discontinuation of SSRIs">
      <data key="d0">Discontinuation of SSRIs</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-6fc0ac2cbfbe29731925a257279ee8f5</data>
      <data key="d2">Stopping or discontinuing SSRI treatment can lead to impotence.</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776221111</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Sexual Symptoms">
