    </node>
    <node id="Insecticides">
      <data key="d0">Insecticides</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Use of insecticides to control the vector is a method of primary prevention for Chagas disease, although its effectiveness is still debated among experts due to the lack of evidence supporting its use. However, some studies indicate that the insecticide pyrethrin can be effective in reducing the transmission of the parasite.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-42e608f979ae406dce55ee3db11f5b0e</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776225962</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="New Construction Compounds">
      <data key="d0">New Construction Compounds</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Use of new construction compounds in building walls and roofs is another method of primary prevention for Chagas disease; however, its effectiveness has not been conclusively proven due to a lack of studies on this specific topic.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-42e608f979ae406dce55ee3db11f5b0e</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776225962</data>
