      <data key="d1">medicalprocedure</data>
      <data key="d2">Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI) can be used for diagnosing aortic stenosis.&lt;SEP&gt;MRI is the diagnostic study of choice for meningioma, though it is not always feasible or necessary due to patient contraindications.&lt;SEP&gt;Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI) is considered the gold standard for diagnosing lumbosacral hemangioma due to its high sensitivity and specificity.</data>
