      <data key="d3">chunk-edd1b5df83b2e724f45910a954f75413</data>
      <data key="d2">Lateral graphy (radiography) is an imaging technique used to visualize median sternotomy wires and CABG clips.</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776236581</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Granulocytopenia">
      <data key="d0">Granulocytopenia</data>
      <data key="d1">symptom</data>
      <data key="d2">Granulocytopenia, or low white blood cell count, increases susceptibility to infections like fungal meningitis.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8bfa6d6104ce651a3fa698d413435e00</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776237157</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="IV Drug Abuse">
      <data key="d0">IV Drug Abuse</data>
      <data key="d1">riskfactor</data>
      <data key="d2">Intravenous drug abuse can increase the risk of exposure to fungal pathogens that cause meningitis.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8bfa6d6104ce651a3fa698d413435e00</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776237157</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Prolonged Intravenous Therapy">
      <data key="d0">Prolonged Intravenous Therapy</data>
      <data key="d1">medicationadministration</data>
      <data key="d2">Prolonged use of intravenous therapy increases the chance of fungal contamination and infection, including fungal meningitis.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8bfa6d6104ce651a3fa698d413435e00</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776237157</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Exposure History">
      <data key="d0">Exposure History</data>
      <data key="d1">riskfactor</data>
      <data key="d2">Traveling to or residing in areas endemic for the pathogen increases the risk of acquiring fungal meningitis.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8bfa6d6104ce651a3fa698d413435e00</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776237157</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Immune Suppression Status">
      <data key="d0">Immune Suppression Status</data>
      <data key="d1">condition</data>
      <data key="d2">Human immunodeficiency virus (HIV) / acquired immunodeficiency syndrome (AIDS) patients have compromised immune systems, making them more susceptible to infections such as fungal meningitis.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8bfa6d6104ce651a3fa698d413435e00</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776237157</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Systemic Neoplasia">
      <data key="d0">Systemic Neoplasia</data>
      <data key="d1">medicalcondition</data>
      <data key="d2">Systemic neoplasia refers to cancer that has spread throughout the body and can compromise the immune system's ability to fight off infections like fungal meningitis.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8bfa6d6104ce651a3fa698d413435e00</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776237157</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Organ Transplantation">
      <data key="d0">Organ Transplantation</data>
      <data key="d1">method</data>
      <data key="d2">Organ transplantation can impair the immune system, increasing susceptibility to infections such as fungal meningitis.&lt;SEP&gt;Similarly, rare cases of transmission have also been documented through organ transplantation between infected and non-infected individuals.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-8bfa6d6104ce651a3fa698d413435e00&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-71d3e3ed160825450fbb193149e7c23d</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776243759</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Tumor Lysis Syndrome">
      <data key="d0">Tumor Lysis Syndrome</data>
      <data key="d1">concept</data>
      <data key="d2">Tumor lysis syndrome is a medical condition that occurs when cancer cells are rapidly destroyed.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-49ab824223b2cb236dc5551487939dab</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776237305</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Cardiac Arrhythmia">
      <data key="d0">Cardiac Arrhythmia</data>
      <data key="d1">condition</data>
      <data key="d2">Cardiac arrhythmias can occur as a result of tumor lysis syndrome, often requiring prompt treatment to prevent cardiac complications.&lt;SEP&gt;Cardiac arrhythmia refers to an irregular heartbeat, which can lead to exercise intolerance.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-49ab824223b2cb236dc5551487939dab&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cbac6ca9c4de60d11284fef00668f6dc</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776248398</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Tetany">
      <data key="d0">Tetany</data>
      <data key="d1">symptom</data>
      <data key="d2">Tetany, or muscle cramps and spasms, is another potential physical examination finding in patients with tumor lysis syndrome.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-49ab824223b2cb236dc5551487939dab</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776237305</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Organism (Cancer Cells)">
      <data key="d0">Organism (Cancer Cells)</data>
      <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
      <data key="d2">Cancer cells are the primary cause of tumor lysis syndrome, leading to inflammation and disruption in bodily functions.</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-49ab824223b2cb236dc5551487939dab</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776237305</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Fever and Tachycardia">
      <data key="d0">Fever and Tachycardia</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-49ab824223b2cb236dc5551487939dab</data>
      <data key="d2">Fever and tachycardia often occur together as side effects of tumor lysis syndrome.</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776237306</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Tumor Lysis Syndrome and Cardiac Arrhythmia">
      <data key="d0">Tumor Lysis Syndrome and Cardiac Arrhythmia</data>
      <data key="d3">chunk-49ab824223b2cb236dc5551487939dab</data>
      <data key="d2">Prompt treatment is necessary to prevent severe cardiac complications associated with cardiac arrhythmias.</data>
      <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
      <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d5">1776237306</data>
      <data key="d6" />
    </node>
    <node id="Side Effects">
      <data key="d0">Side Effects</data>
