    <edge source="Gastrointestinal Bleeding" target="Warfarin">
      <data key="d7">7.0</data>
      <data key="d8">Warfarin significantly increases the risk of severe gastrointestinal bleeding when combined with Aspirin.&lt;SEP&gt;The combination of Warfarin significantly increases the risk of gastrointestinal bleeding.&lt;SEP&gt;The combination of Warfarin and other medications like Lisinopril significantly increases the risk of gastrointestinal bleeding.&lt;SEP&gt;The use of Warfarin increases the risk of gastrointestinal bleeding.&lt;SEP&gt;Taking Warfarin increases the risk of severe gastrointestinal bleeding due to its anticoagulant effects.&lt;SEP&gt;The combination of Warfarin with other medications like Aspirin increases the risk of gastrointestinal bleeding.&lt;SEP&gt;The anticoagulant Warfarin increases the risk of gastrointestinal bleeding when combined with Aspirin.</data>
      <data key="d9">adverse effect,adverse outcome,causal risk factor,contraindication,drug interaction,high risk,increased risk,side effect enhancement</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-185e181fe87408ed68fffee05c4bf2c1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-052d9f2eb36a76fdb7920ef60341853c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-120f6a61156fe5cb9fa55fd78d0d09df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6c01ebde56aad2ac664ce27bcf95cd5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-81ca909fcf7ec8b326421ab4d2766d19&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2258cc9d8db0680e066bcf3b3675f10c</data>
