    <edge source="Gastrointestinal Bleeding" target="Aspirin and Warfarin">
      <data key="d7">12.0</data>
      <data key="d8">Aspirin and Warfarin, Gastrointestinal Bleeding

The combination of Aspirin and Warfarin significantly increases the risk of gastrointestinal bleeding. This increased risk is observed regardless of dosage or frequency of use.

A study conducted by [ undisclosed researchers ] found that combining Aspirin with Warfarin raised the risk of severe gastrointestinal bleeding in patients taking both medications.

Combining Aspirin with Warfarin significantly increases the risk of gastrointestinal bleeding due to their mechanism of action on platelet aggregation and coagulation pathways.

It is crucial for healthcare providers to be aware of this potential interaction when prescribing these medications, particularly in patients at high risk for bleeding complications.&lt;SEP&gt;The combination of Aspirin and Warfarin significantly increases the risk of gastrointestinal bleeding.&lt;SEP&gt;The combination of Aspirin and Warfarin significantly increases the risk of gastrointestinal bleeding due to synergistic anticoagulant effects.&lt;SEP&gt;Combining Aspirin with Warfarin significantly increases the risk of severe gastrointestinal bleeding.&lt;SEP&gt;(No change needed)</data>
      <data key="d9">adverse outcome,increased risk</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-e7a9cdc05d05872d2efc5bf2a78744d8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-96246f0053db41bc6854767c93a37e6c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a037de6f2fcc6d8499a41fc6d0ae4590&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a5a80498abe28fa59b46e83f179e390b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0392546b4be8990b5651990bc3c882c3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7ba9ca889a884bf086782a96a1c01374&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0d9df8319256ab3c418f8c73ac00fad8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f7c0f69e36eeb5da53429b84ed908e5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-05a062c31232f7d983bd96c0052adfc7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e3a0c8e154e4ccec7970a27ed87dde58&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2789d641115d5adedba14603fd459ede</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1776244705</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Gastrointestinal Bleeding" target="COX-1 and COX-2 Enzymes">
      <data key="d7">3.0</data>
      <data key="d8">Aspirin's impact on the gastrointestinal system is closely linked to its effects on COX enzymes.&lt;SEP&gt;The COX pathway is involved in inflammation and bleeding.&lt;SEP&gt;The inhibition of COX-1 and COX-2 enzymes by Aspirin significantly increases the risk of gastrointestinal bleeding.</data>
      <data key="d9">adverse outcome,increased risk,reduction,therapeutic effect</data>
