    <edge source="Aspirin" target="COX-1 and COX-2 Enzymes">
      <data key="d7">9.0</data>
      <data key="d8">Aspirin is a medication that functions by irreversibly inhibiting both COX-1 and COX-2 enzymes. This inhibition results in the reduction of inflammation, as it prevents the production of prostaglandins, which are pro-inflammatory mediators. Additionally, aspirin does not target these enzymes directly but rather works through reversible interactions with specific binding sites on their active sites.

The irreversible nature of this interaction is a key factor in aspirin's mechanism of action, leading to prolonged inhibition of COX-1 and COX-2 enzymes. This effect contributes to its anti-inflammatory properties, making it an effective treatment for conditions such as pain relief and reducing inflammation associated with various diseases.

It's worth noting that the term "irreversible" may cause some confusion in describing this interaction, but this is a more accurate description of how aspirin functions than simply stating it directly inhibits these enzymes. Aspirin functions by irreversibly inhibiting COX-1 and COX-2 enzymes to reduce inflammation in various conditions and diseases.

In summary, the function of aspirin as an inhibitor of COX-1 and COX-2 enzymes is crucial for its therapeutic effects, particularly in reducing inflammation and pain.&lt;SEP&gt;Aspirin targets both COX-1 and COX-2 enzymes, rather than targeting just one as previously stated.</data>
      <data key="d9">inhibition,mechanism of action,target enzyme</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-a45c0433e861eaa94dbda4172985c8d7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2f8e3840cde7d092cb7e453428087efd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e29dee1ec3e83daa8c3982ec784f54d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0392546b4be8990b5651990bc3c882c3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8928c0908948420f48174742a70957ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f7c0f69e36eeb5da53429b84ed908e5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-81ca909fcf7ec8b326421ab4d2766d19&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2258cc9d8db0680e066bcf3b3675f10c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e3a0c8e154e4ccec7970a27ed87dde58</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1776238551</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
