    </edge>
    <edge source="Ichthyosis Vulgaris" target="Rough Palms">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">Rough palms are a characteristic feature of ichthyosis vulgaris.</data>
      <data key="d9">symptom</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-7714b28896e0f4b35847062fac4e9375</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1776207764</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Ichthyosis Vulgaris" target="Severe Ichthyosis Case">
      <data key="d7">3.0</data>
      <data key="d8">Areas of the body not affected by scaly buildup, such as those with sweat glands, are less irritated due to ichthyosis vulgaris.&lt;SEP&gt;The presence of ichthyosis vulgaris leads to severe cases characterized by widespread scaly buildup and reduced skin irritation.&lt;SEP&gt;Areas with a high concentration of sweat glands are less affected by scaly buildup in severe cases.</data>
      <data key="d9">causing effect,contrasting effect</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-7714b28896e0f4b35847062fac4e9375</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1776207765</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Mosaic Lines" target="Severe Ichthyosis Case">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">The buildup of scales in severe cases leads to reduced skin irritation, sparing areas with sweat glands.</data>
      <data key="d9">effect</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-7714b28896e0f4b35847062fac4e9375</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1776207765</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Rough Palms" target="Severe Ichthyosis Case">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">The scales in severe cases cause reduced skin irritation, particularly where the skin rubs against other areas.</data>
      <data key="d9">effect</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-7714b28896e0f4b35847062fac4e9375</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1776207764</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Severe Ichthyosis Case" target="Prickly Itch">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">The build-up of scales causes "prickly itch" when sweating is required but cannot be achieved due to scaly buildup.</data>
      <data key="d9">symptom</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-7714b28896e0f4b35847062fac4e9375</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1776207764</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Dengue Fever" target="Postural Hypotension">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">Postural hypotension is a common symptom among dengue fever patients.</data>
      <data key="d9">symptom association</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-9e84e51a732cb67800c6d62a6011dc86</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1776208059</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Dengue Fever" target="Narrow Pulse Pressure">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">A narrow pulse pressure indicates severe dehydration or capillary leak in dengue fever patients.</data>
      <data key="d9">physiological parameter indication</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-9e84e51a732cb67800c6d62a6011dc86</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1776208059</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Dengue Fever" target="Intravascular Volume Depletion">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">Intravascular volume depletion is a critical complication of dengue fever, necessitating prompt treatment.</data>
      <data key="d9">consequence of disease</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-9e84e51a732cb67800c6d62a6011dc86</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1776208060</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Dengue Fever" target="Urine Output Monitoring">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">A patient not urinating at least every 6 hours may indicate intravascular volume depletion due to capillary leak, necessitating observation.</data>
      <data key="d9">warning sign indication</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-9e84e51a732cb67800c6d62a6011dc86</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1776208061</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Dengue Fever" target="Severe Disease Observation">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">Failure to monitor for severe disease progression can lead to poor outcomes.</data>
      <data key="d9">consequence of inaction</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-9e84e51a732cb67800c6d62a6011dc86</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1776208062</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Dengue Fever" target="Warning Signs for Severe Disease Observation">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">The absence of urination every 6 hours can serve as a warning sign indicating the development of severe disease in dengue fever patients.</data>
      <data key="d9">indication</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-9e84e51a732cb67800c6d62a6011dc86</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1776208063</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Patient" target="Hospitalization">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">Patients with dengue fever should be hospitalized for close monitoring of their condition.</data>
      <data key="d9">recommendation for severe disease observation</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-9e84e51a732cb67800c6d62a6011dc86</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1776208059</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Patient" target="Palpitations">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">Patients often present with a flip flopping, fluttering, pounding or thud like sensation in one particular area or all over the precordium when experiencing palpitations.</data>
      <data key="d9">clinical presentation</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-e521741147e08defca5beb7c20e86d2a</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1776215664</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Patient" target="Endometrial Ablation">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">Endometrial ablation is typically performed on patients who experience severe or prolonged bleeding issues.</data>
      <data key="d9">clinical indication,target population</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-40324022a0e3a72859b0d0b0a9c2b089</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1776217036</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Lithium" target="SLE">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">Lithium may exacerbate or trigger SLE symptoms in some patients.</data>
      <data key="d9">related medical condition,risk factor</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-45f5eef5fb698de7d32f0f45d9ceb869</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1776208684</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Lithium" target="Immune Thrombocytopenic Purpura">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">Lithium use has been associated with increased risk of ITP in some patients.</data>
      <data key="d9">related medical condition,risk factor</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-45f5eef5fb698de7d32f0f45d9ceb869</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1776208686</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Radiation Therapy in Hodgkin's Lymphoma" target="Corticosteroids in Cushing's Syndrome">
      <data key="d7">2.0</data>
      <data key="d8">The concurrent use of radiation therapy and corticosteroid treatment is generally contraindicated due to increased risk of complications.&lt;SEP&gt;The use of radiation therapy for Hodgkin's lymphoma may be combined with corticosteroid treatment for Cushing's syndrome.</data>
      <data key="d9">concurrent use,contraindication,treatment protocol</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-45f5eef5fb698de7d32f0f45d9ceb869</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1776208684</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Corticosteroids in Cushing's Syndrome" target="SLE">
      <data key="d7">2.0</data>
      <data key="d8">Corticosteroid treatment may be used to manage SLE symptoms alongside corticosteroid treatment for Cushing's syndrome.&lt;SEP&gt;Corticosteroid treatment may be used to manage SLE symptoms.</data>
      <data key="d9">concurrent use,related medical condition,treatment protocol</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-45f5eef5fb698de7d32f0f45d9ceb869</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1776208685</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Immune Thrombocytopenic Purpura" target="Lymphocytic Hypophysitis">
      <data key="d7">2.0</data>
      <data key="d8">Both ITP and lymphocytic hypophysitis have autoimmune origins with potential implications for thyroid function.&lt;SEP&gt;Both ITP and lymphocytic hypophysitis are autoimmune conditions with potential links to thyroid dysfunction.</data>
      <data key="d9">related medical condition,risk factor</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-45f5eef5fb698de7d32f0f45d9ceb869</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1776208684</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Antipsychotics" target="Thrombocytopenia">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">Certain antipsychotic medications can increase the risk of thrombocytopenia in patients.</data>
      <data key="d9">risk factor,side effect</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-45f5eef5fb698de7d32f0f45d9ceb869</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1776208684</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="Antipsychotics" target="Thyroid-Stimulating Hormone">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">The use of thyroid-stimulating hormone (TSH) therapy may be contraindicated in patients taking certain antipsychotic medications due to potential interactions and adverse effects.</data>
