    <edge source="Levo-Transposition of the Great Arteries" target="Definition">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">The levo-transposition of the great arteries is defined as an abnormality in which the aorta arises from the right ventricle and the pulmonary artery arises from the left ventricle.</data>
