    <edge source="BARI Trial" target="PTCA">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">The BARI trial examined the effectiveness of PTCA versus CABG for coronary artery disease treatment.</data>
      <data key="d9">clinical indication,treatment</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-2f9dbbcfc70eb17be913a3d7973ef92e</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1776240728</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="BARI Trial" target="CABG">
      <data key="d7">2.0</data>
      <data key="d8">In the BARI trial, a significant difference between PTCA and CABG became apparent in late outcomes such as need for repeat revascularization procedures and symptom status.&lt;SEP&gt;At seven year follow-up interval, early and late survival rates were found to be equivalent for PTCA and CABG patients.</data>
      <data key="d9">equivalent survival rates,late differences,therapy outcome</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-2f9dbbcfc70eb17be913a3d7973ef92e</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1776240728</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="BARI Trial" target="Multiple Severe Lesions">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">The survival advantage for CABG was particularly pronounced in patients with multiple severe lesions.</data>
      <data key="d9">patient subgroup,treatment</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-2f9dbbcfc70eb17be913a3d7973ef92e</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1776240730</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="EAST Trial" target="PTCA">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">The EAST trial also compared PTCA and CABG in treating coronary artery disease.</data>
      <data key="d9">clinical indication,treatment</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-2f9dbbcfc70eb17be913a3d7973ef92e</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1776240728</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="PTCA" target="Revascularization Procedures">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">Patients who underwent PTCA had a higher rate of subsequent revascularization procedures during the five-year follow-up period compared to those in the CABG group.</data>
      <data key="d9">patient outcome,treatment</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-2f9dbbcfc70eb17be913a3d7973ef92e</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1776240729</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="PTCA" target="Angina Rate">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">The rate of freedom from angina was better in patients who underwent CABG and took fewer anti-anginal medications.</data>
      <data key="d9">symptom status,therapy outcome</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-2f9dbbcfc70eb17be913a3d7973ef92e</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1776240730</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="CABG" target="Revascularization Procedures">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">Patients in the CABG group required fewer revascularization procedures compared to those who underwent PTCA.</data>
      <data key="d9">patient outcome,treatment</data>
      <data key="d10">chunk-2f9dbbcfc70eb17be913a3d7973ef92e</data>
      <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
      <data key="d12">1776240728</data>
      <data key="d13" />
    </edge>
    <edge source="CABG" target="Anti-anginal Medications">
      <data key="d7">1.0</data>
      <data key="d8">Fewer patients in the CABG groups needed to take anti-anginal medications compared to those treated with PTCA.</data>
      <data key="d9">medication requirement,therapy outcome</data>
